00:00:56.406 --> 00:01:00.336 A:middle
And then in iOS 9 we
significantly increased the

00:01:00.336 --> 00:01:03.326 A:middle
scope and introduced
sources like music,

00:01:03.856 --> 00:01:06.206 A:middle
currency conversions,
live sports scores,

00:01:06.206 --> 00:01:07.826 A:middle
web, and much, much more.

00:01:07.826 --> 00:01:11.386 A:middle
Perhaps most importantly,
we introduced simple

00:01:11.386 --> 00:01:14.936 A:middle
and powerful ways in which we
could make your apps content

00:01:14.936 --> 00:01:16.166 A:middle
searchable through Spotlight.

00:01:16.546 --> 00:01:20.436 A:middle
So in iOS 10, today we
are announcing extensions

00:01:20.596 --> 00:01:24.086 A:middle
of these Search APIs that will
provide even deeper search

00:01:24.086 --> 00:01:25.156 A:middle
of your app's content.

00:01:25.806 --> 00:01:30.126 A:middle
We've also made Spotlight easier
to use and easier to find.

00:01:30.126 --> 00:01:34.816 A:middle
So let me start by showing
you some examples of things

00:01:34.816 --> 00:01:36.486 A:middle
that we've done to Spotlight.

00:01:37.816 --> 00:01:40.606 A:middle
Spotlight is now present
in Notification Center,

00:01:40.876 --> 00:01:44.396 A:middle
which makes it a lot
faster to get to.

00:01:44.466 --> 00:01:45.876 A:middle
Let's look at an example here.

00:01:45.876 --> 00:01:48.286 A:middle
User receives a message
with a question in it.

00:01:48.286 --> 00:01:51.076 A:middle
Very typical thing that happens.

00:01:51.456 --> 00:01:53.476 A:middle
And they want to run
a search to answer it.

00:01:54.046 --> 00:01:57.856 A:middle
Instead of having to quit
messages and go to Home screen,

00:01:57.986 --> 00:02:01.176 A:middle
pull down Spotlight, they can
simply drag Spotlight on top


