of their section,
as you can see here.

00:09:29.116 --> 00:09:36.736 A:middle
And tapping on this takes
the user into your app

00:09:37.136 --> 00:09:38.066 A:middle
with the search query.

00:09:38.246 --> 00:09:41.606 A:middle
So you can continue the search
query inside of the app.

00:09:41.606 --> 00:09:45.066 A:middle
It's super cool.

00:09:46.476 --> 00:09:49.736 A:middle
The second feature we are
introducing is CoreSpotlight

00:09:49.736 --> 00:09:50.106 A:middle
Search API.

00:09:50.136 --> 00:09:54.186 A:middle
It's a slightly overloaded name,
but there what's happening is

00:09:54.186 --> 00:09:57.236 A:middle
that you're adding
all these items

00:09:57.296 --> 00:10:00.756 A:middle
to Spotlight's search
index by CoreSpotlight API.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:09:57.296 --> 00:10:00.756 A:middle
to Spotlight's search
index by CoreSpotlight API.

00:10:01.286 --> 00:10:03.706 A:middle
Wouldn't it be awesome if
you could use this index

00:10:03.956 --> 00:10:05.466 A:middle
to power search inside
your own app?

00:10:05.466 --> 00:10:07.056 A:middle
I think it would be.

00:10:07.056 --> 00:10:09.966 A:middle
And this is exactly what
CoreSpotlight Search API allows

00:10:09.966 --> 00:10:13.056 A:middle
you to do.

00:10:13.206 --> 00:10:14.986 A:middle
The third feature we
are introducing is a way

